We now get to the place where the rubber meets the road by modelling out the people, tools, processes and knowledge that's required for a given business capability instance[^1] within the value stage[^2].

[^1]: Note that while the concept of Business Capability Instance is not part of ArchiMate as an element, the Stealth EA has created a specialization within the Archi tool that allows for that concept to be modelled.

[^2]: Similar to the business capability instance, ArchiMate only has the Value Stream Concept.  While using a composed of relationship between a Value Stream to another Value Stream infers that the linkage is a Value Stream to a Value Strage, for model readability, having a value stage specialization makes curating the overall enterprise architecture model much easier.

